gun crazy ( also known as deadly is the female ) is a 1950 film noir directed by joseph h. lewis , and produced by frank king and maurice king . the production features peggy cummins and john dall in a story about the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; of a &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; husband and wife . the screenplay by blacklisted writer dalton trumbo — credited to millard kaufman because of the blacklist — and by mackinlay kantor was based upon a short story by kantor published in 1940 in the saturday evening post . in 1998 , gun crazy was selected for preservation in the united states national film registry by the library of congress as being " culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant . "